# SceneSetupSystem  (sbx)

## Purpose
One-shot scene builder. Returns early until SandboxConfigSingletonComponent,
EngineConfigSingletonComponent, and ResourceMapSingletonComponent are all present. On the first ready
frame it creates the 2D scene (the orthographic scene camera, the static demo sprite, the
arrow-key-controlled animated character — a SpriteComponent + an 8x8 SpriteAnimationComponent + a
CharacterTagComponent, starting idle — and the world-space labels) and the 3D demo scene: a
PerspectiveCameraComponent looking at the world origin, a spinning model entity (a ModelComponent
referencing the configured model by UUID + a ModelSpinComponent so ModelSpinSystem rotates it about Y;
it carries no Quad/Sprite, so it lives only in the 3D scene), and a display sprite — a SpriteComponent
textured with the 3D render target (its UUID from the engine config), placed at the centre of the 2D
world to show the 3D image. It also creates the three text-to-image pipeline display sprites bound to
the result-texture UUIDs (`k_BackgroundTextureID`, `k_HintTextureID`, `k_CompositeTextureID`), placed
left to right — the restyled background, the OpenPose pose hint, and the final composite (ADR 0011):
until ImageGenDemoSystem's pipeline registers each step's result that UUID is unregistered and the
renderer falls back to the default texture; once a step finishes, ResourceManagerSystem registers its
result under the matching UUID and it appears in that sprite. Each entity's world transform is seeded
with a SceneTransformRequestOneFrameComponent (position-only for the camera). It also emits a
LoadLayoutEvent to load the UI layout and creates SceneReadySingletonComponent as its run-once guard.

## Input Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| SandboxConfigSingletonComponent | read | Font/texture/model/layout ids for the scene; guard (returns early if absent) |
| EngineConfigSingletonComponent | read | 3D render-target UUID (the display sprite's texture); guard (returns early if absent) |
| ResourceMapSingletonComponent | read | Guard only: ensures the layout load will resolve |
| SceneReadySingletonComponent | read | Run-once guard |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| OrthographicCameraComponent | add (deferred) | 2D scene camera; the app CameraControlSystem drives it via the engine CameraSystem |
| PerspectiveCameraComponent | add (deferred) | Engine component; the 3D camera looking at the spinning model, read by the engine Renderer3DSystem |
| SpriteComponent | add (deferred) | Engine component; the static demo sprite, the animated character's sprite, the 3D-render-target display sprite, and the three text-to-image pipeline display sprites (background, pose hint, composite) |
| SpriteAnimationComponent | add (deferred) | Engine component; the character's 8x8 sprite-sheet animation state (starts idle), driven by the engine SpriteAnimationSystem |
| ModelComponent | add (deferred) | Engine component; references the configured 3D model resource by UUID, drawn by the engine Renderer3DSystem |
| ModelSpinComponent | add (deferred) | Spin parameters for the 3D model, driven by ModelSpinSystem |
| CharacterTagComponent | add (deferred) | Marks the character for CharacterControlSystem |
| LabelComponent | add (deferred) | Title, instructions and the input-readout label |
| SceneTransformRequestOneFrameComponent | add (oneframe) | Seeds the world transform for the cameras, sprites, model and labels |
| InputReadoutTagComponent | add (deferred) | Marks the readout label for InputReadoutSystem |
| LoadLayoutEvent | add (deferred) | Emitted once to load the UI layout |
| SceneReadySingletonComponent | add (deferred) | Run-once guard |
